======================
Referencable objects.
======================

**Referencable objects in Python.**


.. code :: python

    from ref_type import ref


    ref1: ref[int] = ref(1)
    ref2: ref[int] = ref(1)


    def add(r1: ref[int], r2: ref[int]) -> None:
        r1 += r2


    add(ref1, ref2)

    print(ref1) # => 2


Use `.get()` to get value, `.ilshift(X)` to do LeftShiftEquals.
